722814f-a.text:
Riverside Drive, north from 156th Street, showing the semi-rural condition of the street.
About 1918.

MAY BE REPRODUCED>
Neg: 2822

(Based on houses that exist and don't, and the condition of Boulevard Lafayette/Riverside Drive, this is probably 1908 or earlier, not 1918.)

722815f-a.text:
Riverside Drive, east side, from but not including 158th Street, to but not including 160th Streets. (There is no 159th Street on Riverside Drive.
September 25, 1921.
Gift of E. H. Jenks.

722812f-a.text:
839 to 853 Riverside Drive, west side, north of West 158th Street, showing three apartment houses, one on the left and the other two
forming a right angle.
About 1921.
Gift of E.M. Jenks.

722813f-a.text:
839-853 Riverside Drive, west side, north of 158th Street. The photographer is viewing southeastward; the Drive veering east at this point.
About 1924.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.

715696f-a.text:
West 158th Street, west from Riverside Drive to the North (Hudson River). Shown in the center is the elevated West Side Vehicular Highway
against the Palisades of New Jersey.
November 18, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
